tip.text: Sarawakian menu on the list.. Albeit u got to try it to see if it is up for your taste.. So far so good..
So far tried the cornbeef fried rice. Quite good, not that salty as some claim.. Will try the koloks for my next visit.. It got open air and air conditioned dining room..

venue.name: Restoran Cina Muslim Mohd Chan Abdullah

tip.text: Depending on your taste.. Most of the time i'll go for fish snacks. It offered US style fish and chips menus. From spagetti to fish and chips to an exotic zesty tropical drinks i would say.
A long way beach opposing andaman sea. The low tide stretch miles of the beach. Along the shoreline you could get seafood, bars and all sort of light entertainment.
